.TH "dev_get_alias" 9 "dev_get_alias" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dev_get_alias \- get ifalias of a device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dev_get_alias
.BI "(const struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "char *name "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device
.IP "name" 12
buffer to store name of ifalias
.IP "len" 12
size of buffer

get ifalias for a device.  Caller must make sure dev cannot go
away,  e.g. rcu read lock or own a reference count to device.
